You go in order of viscosity, so mists, toners, serums,, and the like go before a cream based product. This allows for the maximum amount of benefit since a lower viscosity = smaller particles = the ability to penetrate deeper into your skin. Ideally, you layer the oil first and then WAIT â€” if you let the oil sink into the skin, you can seal in all the moisture with that wondrous night cream AND still get all the nourishing properties of a water based cream. I am assuming the oil you're using is lighter than the cream â€” if it's not, you COULD switch it around if you want to, but the key is in waiting. If you don't wait, it doesn't matter what order you do them, they will both interfere with each other.
